Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.27,0:00:08.23,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Conny?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.60,0:02:15.73,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- Come on, wait for me!\N- Good morning!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.23,0:02:17.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Good morning!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.90,0:02:19.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Phil! No running!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.86,0:02:21.11,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Does this go here?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.11,0:02:22.49,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.32,0:02:25.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Mark, can you set the table?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.28,0:02:26.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, Mom!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.66,0:02:34.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Good morning, Emma!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.21,0:02:41.67,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Smile, Emma.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.13,0:02:48.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Listen, Emma.\NWe have to behave like we normally do.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.14,0:02:52.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yesterday, we broke the rules\Nand went to the gate.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.39,0:02:55.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But we didn't find anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.69,0:02:57.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But Little Bunny...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.98,0:03:03.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, Mom probably found it.\NBut she doesn't know who left it there.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.49,0:03:08.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Mom was smiling.\NShe doesn't show it on her face at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.95,0:03:10.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And that's what we have to do, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.29,0:03:13.33,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If our faces show it, Mom will notice.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.08,0:03:17.33,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We can't lose. Let's smile.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.01,0:03:29.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The delicious feed, the white clothes where\Ndirt can easily stand out, the well-regulated life...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.93,0:03:33.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This is all to maintain\Nour quality as merchandise.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.14,0:03:38.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The only thing we can do is to wait\Nas we are shipped out indiscriminately.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.60,0:03:41.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's not indiscriminately.\NRemember what the demon said?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.73,0:03:45.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,"Another six-year-old. We've been\Nshipping out normal quality ones."
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.03,0:03:46.24,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What does that mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.24,0:03:50.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Judging from those words,\Nage probably equals the grade of meat.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.82,0:03:52.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If I remember correctly,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.74,0:03:56.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,the siblings who were shipped out\Nwere between six and twelve years old.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.71,0:04:00.63,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If being six years old is ranked as normal,\Nthen the highest quality is...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.00,0:04:02.17,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Twelve years old.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.50,0:04:03.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But what about our scores?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.96,0:04:07.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Meat won't taste better even if we get\Ngood scores on tests, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.80,0:04:12.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. It was never announced\Nunless we got full scores, but maybe...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.18,0:04:14.47,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The order of getting shipped out?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.47,0:04:18.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,After we turn six, we get harvested\Nstarting from the lower test scores.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.48,0:04:23.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And when we turn 12,\Nwe get shipped out no matter what.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.40,0:04:28.07,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So we were never shipped out\Nbecause we have full scores?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.49,0:04:32.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But I don't understand\Nwhy it depends on our scores.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.99,0:04:37.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Is there meaning for being between\Nthe age of six and twelve?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.33,0:04:39.83,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The size of our bodies?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.46,0:04:42.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No. Then it would depend on our weight.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.88,0:04:47.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The size of our brains.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.72,0:04:49.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That means...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.84,0:04:51.55,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The brain probably tastes the best.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.22,0:04:55.43,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}And the more developed brain, the better.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.81,0:04:58.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Eating... the brain?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.27,0:05:01.77,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}And they don't care\Nhow much they risk or spend.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.10,0:05:04.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}That's why we're high-quality merchandise.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.36,0:05:05.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Try to remember, Emma.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.07,0:05:09.49,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Conny was shipped out. Before her was Hao.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.70,0:05:11.32,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Before him was Sadie.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.53,0:05:16.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Based on the cycle so far, the next shipment\Nshould be two months from now at the earliest.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.87,0:05:21.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}We need to think of a way\Nfor all of us to escape before then.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.05,0:05:33.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If we draw a simple map of this site,\Nthe House is in the middle and then the gate.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.05,0:05:36.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And the forest that surrounds us.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.76,0:05:41.27,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,First, which one should we escape from?\NThe gate or the forest?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.14,0:05:44.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe the forest?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.19,0:05:48.11,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The gate is always closed except during shipping,\Nand when it's open...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.11,0:05:49.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The demons are there.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.07,0:05:52.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,When do we escape through the forest?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.32,0:05:55.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,At playtime, during the day,\Nwhen we can get out of the House freely?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.28,0:05:57.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Or at night during shipping when Mom is not—
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.58,0:06:01.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Not during shipping!\NSomeone will definitely get sacrificed.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.75,0:06:02.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.12,0:06:06.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And I'm worried if the younger ones\Ncan stay awake at night.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.34,0:06:08.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Then it's decided.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.63,0:06:12.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We'll escape during the day through the forest.\NWhether that's possible...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.51,0:06:15.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Depends on what it's like beyond the forest.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.36,0:06:30.53,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Norman!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.82,0:06:38.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Norman! Are you okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.33,0:06:42.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I guess I'm tired from thinking too much.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.71,0:06:47.29,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Sheesh, I guess it can't be helped.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.21,0:06:53.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So? Is something there?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.05,0:06:55.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.43,0:06:58.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But this wall is about two to three meters thick.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.68,0:07:00.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And it's pretty tall.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.93,0:07:02.73,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But there are no guards.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.14,0:07:05.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's quiet.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.98,0:07:08.73,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What do you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.82,0:07:12.23,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's hard and sturdy.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.94,0:07:15.49,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,There are no edges, let alone any seams.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.49,0:07:17.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And the surface is smooth.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.74,0:07:19.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,There's no way anyone could climb this.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.99,0:07:21.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Then should we give up?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.91,0:07:24.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But that's what this wall would have us think.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.46,0:07:28.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If it was you or me,\Nwe could climb it as long as we had a rope.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.71,0:07:30.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I don't sense any demons around.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.88,0:07:32.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The only one watching us is Mom.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.80,0:07:34.59,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry. It's not scary.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.10,0:07:45.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Two kids are missing.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.48,0:07:46.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Mom!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.98,0:07:48.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Mark!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.44,0:07:51.77,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Did something happen?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.61,0:07:56.49,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What should I do?\NI got separated from Naila in the forest!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.49,0:07:59.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I tried looking, but I couldn't find her!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.79,0:08:07.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It'll be okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.25,0:08:11.29,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone, stay here.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.84,0:08:12.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Understood?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.97,0:08:17.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Mom.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.23,0:08:29.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Mom!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.06,0:08:30.35,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Naila!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.35,0:08:31.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,She got tired and fell asleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.52,0:08:34.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Look, not a scratch on her.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.86,0:08:36.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Thank goodness!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.19,0:08:40.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm so sorry, Naila. I'm sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.24,0:08:44.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It was like Mom knew\Nexactly where Naila was.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.29,0:08:51.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Come to think of it,\NMom has always been good at finding us.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.33,0:08:54.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No matter where we hid, she found us quickly.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.38,0:08:56.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's not a pocket watch.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.01,0:08:58.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Tracking devices.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.97,0:09:02.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,They could be implanted\Nsomewhere in our bodies.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.01,0:09:08.35,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And Mom used the compact and purposely\Nshowed us so we would figure it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.10,0:09:10.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,"No matter who it is, I won't let you escape."
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.40,0:09:14.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's probably what Mom wants to say.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.99,0:09:21.11,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Mom is...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.70,0:09:22.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...an enemy.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.21,0:09:36.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,First, let's get our hands on some rope.\NI have an idea where they might be.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.46,0:09:38.05,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'll see you tonight at 10 in the hallway.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.21,0:09:39.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.80,0:09:42.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,They have tracking devices on us,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.18,0:09:45.05,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,so what if they have other stuff,\Nlike cameras or listening devices?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.43,0:09:46.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.68,0:09:50.43,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I looked around a bit,\Nand there was nothing like that here.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.43,0:09:51.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,When did you do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.56,0:09:53.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But I should have known.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.56,0:09:57.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The security measures\Naren't on the building, but on us.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.90,0:10:00.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Do you think Mom knows already?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.78,0:10:03.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That we went all the way to the wall...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.99,0:10:05.24,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I don't think so.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.57,0:10:07.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I mean, she didn't know\Nabout that other time, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.04,0:10:10.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,When we went to deliver Little Bunny.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.16,0:10:12.08,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.58,0:10:16.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's not like Mom always knows\Nwhere we are at all times.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.59,0:10:18.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,She'll know our location only when she checks.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.71,0:10:24.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,She knows that Little Bunny was brought\Nto the gate by someone other than Conny.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.43,0:10:29.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But I don't think she figured out who it was.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.22,0:10:32.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Or else she wouldn't have warned us\Nin such a roundabout way.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.10,0:10:32.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.98,0:10:34.81,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Norman!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.81,0:10:36.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Do you have a second?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.19,0:10:38.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The clock isn't quite working properly.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.48,0:10:40.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, I'll take a look.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.07,0:10:42.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It'll be okay, Emma.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.07,0:10:45.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We're not being suspected.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.33,0:10:58.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Conny.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.93,0:11:05.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Em—
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.06,0:11:12.43,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong, Emma?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.64,0:11:14.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You look pale.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.10,0:11:21.53,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Which reminds me,\Nyou weren't so cheerful this morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.07,0:11:23.24,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's not...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.75,0:11:38.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.58,0:11:43.63,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I just got a little sad thinking that\NI’ll leave the House soon, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.34,0:11:46.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Do you like it here at the House?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.30,0:11:49.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I love the House and you, Mom!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.01,0:11:54.81,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder what Conny's doing right now?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.90,0:12:06.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Conny said she wanted to be\Na mother like you when she grew up.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.41,0:12:13.41,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.99,0:12:16.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure Conny will become a lovely adult,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.83,0:12:18.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and a good mother, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.09,0:12:24.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Dinner preparations are ready, Mom.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.84,0:12:29.89,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be right there.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.89,0:12:30.97,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Wait for me!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.89,0:12:33.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.72,0:12:36.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Emma, let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.10,0:12:36.77,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.19,0:12:41.77,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Did the two of you...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.31,0:12:44.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,go to the gate yesterday?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.19,0:12:49.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We didn't. That's against the rules.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.61,0:12:52.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, we were having too much fun\Nplaying tag yesterday. Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.70,0:12:53.87,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.87,0:12:54.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.79,0:12:58.87,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's nothing. As long as you didn't go.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.52,0:13:17.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Can you stand up?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.99,0:14:20.08,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This was a really good idea, Norman.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.29,0:14:21.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Using tablecloths.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.29,0:14:24.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This can be used as rope.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.59,0:14:32.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,With this, we can get over the wall.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.39,0:14:36.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Okay. The challenge is still ahead of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.26,0:14:38.81,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Where the tracking devices are...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.31,0:14:41.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...and a way to get everyone out.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.85,0:14:43.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Norman.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.94,0:14:47.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I think it might be fine if we told Ray.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.19,0:14:49.07,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I was thinking that, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.44,0:14:52.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Ray most likely wouldn't panic.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.28,0:14:54.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And because of his extensive knowledge,\Nhe's good with machines, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.28,0:14:57.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure we can depend on him.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.95,0:14:58.87,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.12,0:14:59.83,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.37,0:15:02.33,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'll talk to Ray myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.50,0:15:04.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Why don't you go back, and—
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.04,0:15:05.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.13,0:15:07.13,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Ray!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.25,0:15:10.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yo.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.67,0:15:15.43,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, I followed you guys.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.05,0:15:20.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's been bugging me for a while,\Nso I thought I should ask about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.77,0:15:30.07,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}What happened at the gate that night?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.48,0:15:33.49,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}When you went to go deliver\NLittle Bunny to Conny.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.86,0:15:36.61,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}You were both clearly acting weird.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.61,0:15:39.49,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}And you were empty-handed\Nwhen you said you didn't make it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.58,0:15:40.83,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}You're perceptive.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.04,0:15:43.41,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}So of course something happened. Give it up.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.41,0:15:45.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Ray is smart, too, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.34,0:15:56.59,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Demons... A farm...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.55,0:15:59.35,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Mom is an enemy?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.01,0:16:01.89,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't this bad?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.89,0:16:03.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,He catches on fast!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.35,0:16:10.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So you're saying we were preciously\Ntaken care of to become demon food.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.27,0:16:11.23,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.23,0:16:13.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm surprised you're believing us so easily.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.90,0:16:18.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Of course. Norman wouldn't\Nmake up such a stupid lie.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.32,0:16:20.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}It'd be different with you, Emma.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.16,0:16:27.75,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So, if we're really going to escape,\Nthere are various issues.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.96,0:16:29.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,First, the number of kids.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.00,0:16:32.59,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- We'll narrow it down to who can make it and—\N- Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.17,0:16:36.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}I want to escape with everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.42,0:16:39.13,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Lend us your strength, Ray!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.55,0:16:42.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Everyone?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.01,0:16:44.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}You're kidding, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.14,0:16:47.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}There are 37 of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.35,0:16:49.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}And the majority are under six years old.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.73,0:16:50.31,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Mom.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.77,0:16:51.61,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Demons.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.61,0:16:52.77,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Tracking devices.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.98,0:16:56.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,These factors make an already difficult escape\Neven more challenging.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.90,0:16:58.32,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I know that.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.32,0:16:59.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But it's not impossible—
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.74,0:17:00.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No, it's impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.16,0:17:03.87,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Emma, you haven't noticed, have you?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.58,0:17:05.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Ray, wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.62,0:17:10.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I see. That's why you said\Nyou'll talk to me yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.13,0:17:13.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}You have to be blunt\Nabout these kinds of things.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.71,0:17:14.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Emma.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.71,0:17:15.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}What?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.71,0:17:18.05,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It won't be enough just to escape from here.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.38,0:17:19.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.26,0:17:23.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We don't know what it's like on the outside.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.80,0:17:25.89,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But there's a place we're getting shipped to.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.14,0:17:29.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Because there's a farm,\Nthat should give you an idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.39,0:17:32.73,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What waits outside is a demon's society.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.98,0:17:36.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,There is no place for humans to live.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.86,0:17:40.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}So it's impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.61,0:17:43.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}If we take everyone, we'll all die.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.37,0:17:46.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We leave them behind. That's the best option.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.62,0:17:49.25,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No way.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.17,0:17:53.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Even if it's impossible,\NI want to escape with everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.79,0:17:54.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Let's figure it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.13,0:18:00.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I don't want all of us to die.\NBut there's no option to leave them behind.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.97,0:18:03.93,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I want Conny to be the last.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.43,0:18:07.81,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I don't want anyone\Nto end up like that ever again.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.81,0:18:12.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If there isn’t one, then let's make\Na place for humans to live outside.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.35,0:18:14.81,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Let's change the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.15,0:18:18.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}I understand now, thanks to you, Ray.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.44,0:18:20.61,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}That's the kind of prison break we have to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.90,0:18:22.53,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}I'm not giving up on this.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.24,0:18:24.32,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Because I've decided.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.32,0:18:29.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So, Ray, you're the one who has to give up.\NStop jabbering around and help us!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.17,0:18:36.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Guardian, how can—
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.84,0:18:39.13,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We'll escape with everyone, no matter what!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.13,0:18:41.63,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Or else I won't do it. I won't! I won't!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.63,0:18:44.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Do something about that idiot!\NShe's unreasonable.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.30,0:18:47.89,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I know, right? But I'm glad she's so cheerful.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.89,0:18:51.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I wanted for you to stop her!\NOr you're both going to die.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.02,0:18:54.77,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You knew that from the very start, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.06,0:18:58.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Emma was crying.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.23,0:19:03.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That night, I thought she was crying\Nbecause she was scared.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.07,0:19:05.61,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But I was wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.53,0:19:09.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I was scared of dying.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.37,0:19:13.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But Emma was crying because\Nshe was scared of her family dying.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.71,0:19:19.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that amazing? She thinks of\Nprotecting others in that situation.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.84,0:19:21.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But it's not the correct thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.46,0:19:24.47,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's a boat made of mud!\NAnd it's just us three, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.68,0:19:26.43,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If it's just us, we can escape.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.97,0:19:30.89,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You're correct, and you shouldn't feel ashamed.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.10,0:19:33.81,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Don't distort your decision\Nbased on emotions, Norman!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.19,0:19:35.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's not that, Ray.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.85,0:19:37.73,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I also want to make a boat out of mud.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.61,0:19:42.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Why? Aren't you different?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.07,0:19:45.61,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You're more cool-headed,\Nand you always take the best option.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.95,0:19:47.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So, why?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.95,0:19:49.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Because I like her.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.20,0:19:53.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I like Emma, so that's why\NI want her to always be smiling.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.16,0:19:56.83,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You're crazy.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.12,0:19:59.59,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And what if Emma dies because of it?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.17,0:20:01.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I won't let her die.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.38,0:20:05.63,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's why I'm going to utilize myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.01,0:20:11.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Luckily, I've always managed\Nto accomplish what I set out to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.64,0:20:15.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And if you bake mud, it'll become a vessel.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.35,0:20:18.35,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,A boat made out of mud won't necessarily sink.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.77,0:20:20.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}You're nuts.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.23,0:20:25.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Maybe. Both Emma and I are insane.\NWe've completely lost it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.95,0:20:28.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}You can't let us do this on our own, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.41,0:20:32.49,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Damn it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.04,0:20:35.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Of course I can't.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.58,0:20:39.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Ray. Norman.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.00,0:20:42.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We still have free time left, don't we?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.71,0:20:43.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder what it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.97,0:20:53.35,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Let me introduce her.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.56,0:20:55.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This is your newest little sister, Carol.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.85,0:21:00.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And this is Sister Krone. She's here to help me.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.73,0:21:03.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,A-An adult?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.28,0:21:05.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Another enemy.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.90,0:21:11.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I will be living here with all of you\Nstarting today. It's nice to meet you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.91,0:21:15.08,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- It's nice to meet you.\N- Hello!
